entry.title: Fix PagedAppsGridViewTests to work with drag and drop refactor feature.
entry.content:
This CL will increase coverage and solve some individual bugs related

to the drag and drop refactor implementation.



The test on PagedAppsGridViewTest suite now run with and without the

feature on. In order to properly test the drag and drop refactor, the

suite now injects a loop closure to the DragDropController that handles

actions and checks while the drag is in progress to have more control

over the flow. When the feature is off, the list of tasks set to run

within the DragDropController loop just run synchronously one by one.



Some tests failing for this suite, included a case where the apps grid

would sometimes be translated to a different page when beginning the

drag due to the view not ensuring focus when the drag starts. This is

ensured by SilentlyRequestFocus when AppListItemView::InitiateDrag is

invoked.



Another issue that the tests uncovered, was that when dragging an app

from one page into another page and canceling the drag, the apps grid

will end the drag but not translate the apps grid to the original page

where the drag started, effectively loosing sight of the app. This is

fixed by ensuring that the view is selected when the drag is done.



Bug: b:261985897, b:278121975

entry.title: DevTools: Persist devtools_navigation_token in RFH
entry.content:
We currently use devtools_navigation_token to associate a preloading

attempt with its initiator document. However, we currently send the

token from the renderer back to the browser through a mojo IPC

(SpeculationHost.UpdateSpeculationCandidates), despite this token

having been generated in the browser in the first place (in most

scenarios). With this change, we can now retrieve the token directly

from the initiating RFH in the browser process, instead of resending it

back from the renderer.



This CL stores the devtools_navigation_token from a NavigationRequest

in a RFH after a navigation commits. The token has "per-document"

semantics and is stored in RFH::DocumentAssociatedData. The token isn't set for RFHs with the initial empty document (in these scenarios, the

token is generated in the renderer, and the browser doesn't currently

have access to it). We currently don't have a use case that needs to

access the token in such scenarios, but we could revisit this if we

need to in the future.

entry.title: Open URL upon notification tap when app is closed
entry.content:
When the user taps on a notification, the URL is opened in

Chrome for iOS. Currently if the app is closed when this occurs

the URL is attempted to be opened before any browsers are initialized.

This CL delays the opening of the URL until the app is fully loaded

and the browser is initialized by observing the AppState.



Demo: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1w0oNV0jXJe0Kw6EPlGoa-oj3hsKS54yY/view?usp=sharing



Out of scope:

- Multi window on iPad will be addressed in a separate CL

- It should be considered delaying notification interactions

in the push notification infrastructure until the app is loaded

rather than having individual clients handle it. However, in the

interests of getting a fix out to users quickly this will be

addressed in a separate CL.

a semantic variable i.e color-dark or color-light. This poses a problem

for the use of legacy_mappings as we only map "color" not "color-light"

meaning some subset of UI ignores a specified mapping.



This CL fixes this by forcing all of our legacy mappings to also

generate mappings for light/dark variants. Note that this is also a

problem autogenerated -rgb vars but this is left for a future CL

since it's a more involved change.

entry.title: [VCManager] Forward effects command line flag
entry.content:
Guest mode uses `GetOffTheRecordCommandLine` which does not

forward switches from the base command line implicitly.



This is causing VC features to not work in guest mode.



This fix forwards the `kCameraEffectsSupportedByHardware` switch

to the derived command line allowing VC to work in guest mode.
